From: Mono Gateway ASK <noreply@example.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: dpaa: dpa_get_channel: use mutex not spinlock

dpa_get_channel() takes a spinlock around a qman_alloc_pool() call that
can sleep (it goes through dpa_alloc_new → kmalloc(GFP_KERNEL)). This
tripped CONFIG_DEBUG_ATOMIC_SLEEP on boot:

    BUG: sleeping function called from invalid context at mm.h:321
    in_atomic(): 1, irqs_disabled(): 0
    1 locks held: rx_pool_channel_init (spinlock)
    dpa_alloc_new+0x60 ← qman_alloc_pool_range ← dpa_get_channel
    ← dpaa_eth_priv_probe

The spinlock was protecting a single u32 one-shot init. That init only
runs during probe (process context), so a mutex is the correct primitive
— spinlock here was never justifiable. Under memory pressure this would
genuinely deadlock.

No functional change beyond dropping preempt-disable across the alloc.

---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
index c4db971a4f97..7191856e3424 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
@@ -963,18 +963,24 @@ int dpa_fq_probe_mac(struct device *dev, struct list_head *list,
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(dpa_fq_probe_mac);
 
 static u32 rx_pool_channel;
-static DEFINE_SPINLOCK(rx_pool_channel_init);
+/* qman_alloc_pool() → dpa_alloc_new() → kmalloc(GFP_KERNEL), which may
+ * sleep under direct reclaim. This one-shot init only runs during probe
+ * (process context), so a mutex is the correct primitive — the original
+ * spinlock was an unprovoked atomic-context violation that made
+ * CONFIG_DEBUG_ATOMIC_SLEEP WARN and would deadlock under memory pressure.
+ */
+static DEFINE_MUTEX(rx_pool_channel_init);
 
 int dpa_get_channel(void)
 {
-	spin_lock(&rx_pool_channel_init);
+	mutex_lock(&rx_pool_channel_init);
 	if (!rx_pool_channel) {
 		u32 pool;
 		int ret = qman_alloc_pool(&pool);
 		if (!ret)
 			rx_pool_channel = pool;
 	}
-	spin_unlock(&rx_pool_channel_init);
+	mutex_unlock(&rx_pool_channel_init);
 	if (!rx_pool_channel)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 	return rx_pool_channel;
